President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Jovita Carranza as Administrator of the Small Business Administration. Carranza currently serves as Treasurer of the United States and has previously held the position of Deputy Administrator for the United States Small Business Administration. She has also had a distinguished career at UPS, where she became the highest-ranking Latina in the company's history. 

President Trump has also announced his intent to appoint Kendel S. Ehrlich as Deputy Director of the Office of National Drug Control Policy. Ehrlich currently serves as the Associate Director of External Affairs at the White House Office of National Drug Control Policy and has previously served as a public defender and prosecutor in Maryland. 

In addition, President Trump intends to appoint David John Urban, Guy C. Swan III, and Sean Michael Spicer as members of the Board of Visitors to the United States Military Academy and United States Naval Academy.